criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Males or females over 18 years of age who meet the DSM-5 criteria for CUD (≥4
             criteria) ;

          -  Patients will meet the DSM-5 criteria for schizophrenia, schizoaffective disorder, or
             bipolar disorder with psychotic symptoms. Diagnoses will be established with the
             Structured Interview for DSM-5 (SCID-5).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Current SUD for a substance other than cannabis ;

          -  Ongoing pharmacological or psychological treatment for CUD ;

          -  Ongoing detoxification for cannabis withdrawal ;

          -  Presence of neurological disorders ;

          -  Presence of a severe and unstable physical illness ;

          -  Inability to provide consent.
